This subfolder contains hands-on projects, notebooks, and pipelines that demonstrate how to leverage BigQuery AI to build real-world Generative AI and Machine Learning applications directly inside the data warehouse.

BigQuery AI enables:

ML.GENERATE_TEXT → Run LLMs (e.g., Gemini) inside SQL for text generation, query answering, and reasoning.

ML.GENERATE_EMBEDDING → Convert text, images, and structured data into embeddings for semantic search and retrieval.

VECTOR_SEARCH → Perform similarity search across large-scale embedding tables with millisecond response times.

BigQuery ML Models → Train and deploy traditional models (time-series, regression, classification, uplift modeling).

 Included Projects
 Video Fashion Search

Download YouTube videos and extract frames.

Analyze fashion items with Gemini Vision via ML.GENERATE_TEXT.

Create embeddings of queries and products with ML.GENERATE_EMBEDDING.

Match detected items against a product catalog using VECTOR_SEARCH.

Display results visually with side-by-side comparisons.

- Customer Segmentation & Uplift Modeling

Use RFM features and customer history.

Apply uplift modeling in BigQuery ML to identify “Persuadables” (customers most influenced by campaigns).

Optimize print mailing and digital marketing strategies.

- Text-to-SQL Agent

Natural language → SQL translation using ML.GENERATE_TEXT.

Enables business users to query complex data without writing SQL.

Example: “Show me sales by category in Berlin last quarter” → auto-generated SQL.

- Embedding Search Demo

Generate embeddings for product descriptions and metadata.

Use VECTOR_SEARCH to enable semantic product discovery.

Supports “similar product” search, cross-selling, and personalized recommendations.

-  Why BigQuery AI?

No data movement → AI runs where your data already lives.

Scalable → Handles billions of rows and vectors.

Integrated → Works seamlessly with Vertex AI and Gemini models.

Practical → Real-world applications in retail, finance, and marketing.
